.TH RANCHER-POLYMPH 1 "June 2026" "rancher-polymorph 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rancher-polymorph \- sanitize Rancher backups for migration to a new cluster
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rancher-polymorph
[\fIglobal flags\fR] <command> [command flags]
.PP
.B rancher-polymorph sanitize
.B \-i
\fIINPUT\fR
.B \-o
\fIOUTPUT\fR [options]
.br
.B rancher-polymorph inspect
.B \-i
\fIINPUT\fR
.br
.B rancher-polymorph restore plan
.B \-b
\fIBACKUP_FILE\fR [options]
.br
.B rancher-polymorph manual
[\fItopic\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rancher-polymorph
filters full Rancher backup tarballs so they can be restored on a new management cluster without carrying local-cluster state, removed downstream clusters, or Fleet ghost artifacts.
.PP
Progress and phase logs are written to stderr (or \fB\-\-log\-file\fR). Command results use a summary box on stdout; use \fB\-\-report\fR for the full list of removed paths.
.SH GLOBAL FLAGS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Extra DEBUG lines on stderr / log file.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress progress bar and stderr logs.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show command help.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B sanitize
Filter backup tarball (see \fBSANITIZE\fR).
.TP
.B inspect
Read-only backup analysis (see \fBINSPECT\fR).
.TP
.B restore plan
Emit Restore CR YAML with \fBprune: false\fR.
.TP
.B manual
Print the manual; topics: sanitize, inspect, restore, migration.
.SH MIGRATION FLOW
.IP 1. 3
Take a full backup on the source Rancher.
.IP 2.
\fBrancher-polymorph inspect \-i backup.tar.gz\fR
.IP 3.
\fBrancher-polymorph sanitize \-i backup.tar.gz \-o sanitized.tar.gz \-\-keep-cluster CLUSTER_ID \-\-report report.txt\fR
.IP 4.
Copy sanitized tarball to the restore target storage/PVC.
.IP 5.
\fBrancher-polymorph restore plan \-b sanitized.tar.gz \-o restore.yaml\fR
.IP 6.
Apply restore.yaml while Rancher is NOT running.
.IP 7.
Install cert-manager and Rancher Helm; reconnect RKE1 agents.
.SH SANITIZE
Required: \fB\-\-input\fR / \fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR / \fB\-o\fR
.PP
Cluster selection (one required):
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
\fB\-\-keep-cluster\fR \fIID\fR \(em keep one downstream cluster
.IP \(bu
\fB\-\-keep\-rke1\-only\fR \(em keep every RKE1 cluster
.RE
.PP
Orphan / Fleet cleanup:
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
\fB\-\-remove\-cluster\fR \fIID\fR (repeatable)
.IP \(bu
\fB\-\-no\-auto\-orphans\fR
.RE
.SH INSPECT
Required: \fB\-\-input\fR / \fB\-i\fR
.PP
Reports cluster inventory, Fleet mappings, ghost cluster IDs, and local-cluster references.
.SH RESTORE PLAN
Required: \fB\-\-backup\-file\fR / \fB\-b\fR
.SH FILES
.TP
docs/sanitize-backup-for-restore.md
Extended documentation in this repository.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PAGER
Used by \fBrancher-polymorph manual \-p\fR (default: less).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sanitize-backup-for-restore.py (1)
